The paper deals with improving localization accuracy in connected vehicle networks, which is a problem in robotics and control systems (cs.RO). The proposed approach involves joint estimation of biases and vehicle positions, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and system theory (cs.SY). The use of digital maps and multi-hypothesis detection-rejection approach also involves networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and computer vision (cs.CV).
